The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Wednesday, February 25, 2004 				 Hostage to bandh brigade
 OUR CORRESPONDENTMidnapore, Feb. 24: About 400 Calcutta Port Trust employees who were on morning shift at Haldia dock were locked up inside their offices till late night by strike supporters.																								The employees, both officers and labourers, came on Monday night for the shift that was to begin at 8 am today. When they were about to leave office after work around 6 in the evening, nearly 500 bandh backers blocked their way and forced them inside. Women employees, who were being escorted by CISF jawans, were also prevented from leaving the premises.																								R.K. Burman, the docks administrative officer, said the employees were stuck inside Jawahar Tower, the main administrative building, and the cargo handling office at Chiranjitpur. 																								The bandh supporters said at a meeting with senior port officials that they could release the grade I officers. An official said they rejected the proposal.																								A police team has been sent and it is trying to rescue them, said subdivisional police officer Satyajit Bandyopadhyay. 																								CPM MP from Haldia Lakshman Seth said: I do not know about any such incident. There were no complaints.
